I'm pretty sure this would have worked
Real rho, drho_dp, drho_dT;
_fp.rho_from_p_T(_press[_qp].value(), _temperature[_qp].value, rho, drho_dp, drho_dT);

and if it doesn't, check for typos.
But the
DualReal rho = rho_from_p_T(_press[_qp],  _temperature[_qp]);

calculates exactly the same things. You can get the derivate wrt T using
Real drho_dT = rho.derivatives()[T_index];

where T_index is the index of the temperature variable.

